webpackJsonp([0xbaac6b53cf0],{8316:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Hermann",date:"13 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-13-hermann/",tags:"Y2006"},html:'<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photo_zoom.gne?id=86155837&amp;size=l" title="Photo Sharing"><img src="http://static.flickr.com/38/86155837_80a46c2bc7.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="hermann" /></a></p>\n<p>This is Hermann, our new family member for the next 10 days. Christopher brought him home from Kindergarten, and he seems to be a sourdough of some sort. If we treat him right, he will give birth to 3 Hermann-children, and we can bake a cake.</p>\n<p>Until then, though, he has to be cared for quite carefully.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Day 1. Hermann needs rest. </li>\n<li>Days 2-4. Hermann needs exercise. Stir once each day.</li>\n<li>Day 5. Hermann is hungry! Feed him with 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk. He then needs a bigger bowl, otherwise he will run away.</li>\n<li>Days 6-9. Hermann needs time to digest. He needs a daily walk. Stir once each day.</li>\n<li>Day 10. Feed again with 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>He is then ready to give birth to 3 children (1 cup each, to be given to good friends), and with the rest we can bake a cake (recipe to follow, or just <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photo_zoom.gne?id=86155837&amp;size=l" title="Photo Sharing">click</a> on the photo).</p>\n<p>Christopher has already memorized the instructions and is making sure we follow them to the letter. Today is Day 1, and despite the rest Hermann seems to have a bad case of gas. We\'ve had to open the cover several times.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"It's Your Heimspiel",date:"12 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-12-its-your-heimspiel/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Career Planning",date:"16 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-16-career-planning/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"It's Your Heimspiel",date:"12 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-12-its-your-heimspiel/",tags:"Y2006"},html:'<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/papascott/85538623/" title="Photo Sharing"><img src="http://static.flickr.com/42/85538623_453ad2cade.jpg" width="500" height="207" alt="heimspiel" /></a></p>\n<p>World Cup doesn\'t start until summer, but Mama has already brought home her first World Cup swag. But I don\'t get it. Why the Denglish? We don\'t watch much TV, but apparently this is <a href="http://www.cokefridge.de/">Coca-Cola\'s main advertising slogan</a> in Germany for the tournament. Mama couldn\'t explain it either, she just shrugged and said "It\'s supposed to rhyme".</p>\n<p>So what slogan are they using in the rest of the world, "It\'s your Ausw&auml;rtsspiel"?</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Technical Translation",date:"11 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-11-technical-translation/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Hermann",date:"13 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-13-hermann/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Technical Translation",date:"11 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-11-technical-translation/",tags:"Y2006"},html:'<p>A friend of my sister-in-law is looking for a technical translator, and<br />\nshe thought that perhaps a reader of PapaScott might be qualified and<br />\ninterested in the job:</p>\n<p>"Who is able to either correct a translation of a technical text from<br />\nGerman into English or to translate it totally on his own? The text to<br />\nbe translated is the homepage of a German company (see<br />\n<a href="http://www.sintertechnik.com">http://www.sintertechnik.com</a>), and the translator should have some<br />\nknowledge in areas such as high performance technical ceramics (for<br />\nexample ceramic bearings), development and processing of specific<br />\nceramic powders to the pressing and firing of ceramical parts (like<br />\nspray-dried powders), as well as electroceramics (EMC- Electromagnetic<br />\ncompatibility, VDR - voltage dependant resistors, multilayers, capacitors).</p>\n<p>"If you think that you are the right person for this task, please<br />\ncontact me at <a href="mailto:jurgen@schell.elcom.ru">jurgen@schell.elcom.ru</a>."</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Sticky Hardware",date:"11 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-11-sticky-hardware/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"It's Your Heimspiel",date:"12 Jan 2006",slug:"/2006-01-12-its-your-heimspiel/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:249,pageCount:1101}}}});
